@chapter Synopsis

ohplay [@var{options}] [@file{input_file}]  [@var{options}] [@file{output_file}]

@chapter Description
@c man begin DESCRIPTION

ohplay is a simple HEVC/SHVC player based on OpenHEVC and SDL libraries. 

@c man end

@chapter Options
@c man begin OPTIONS

@table @option

@item -i @file{input_file}
Input file

@item -v
Used to signal the presence of a H264/AVC base layer bitstream 

@item -e @file{enhancement_layer_file}
Used to specify the enhancement layer when it consist of a second bitstream

@item -n
Disable the display

@item -o @file{output_file}
Output raw video to @file{output_file}

@item -c
Do not check md5.

@item -l @var{quality_layer_id}
Used to specify the @var{quality_layer_id} to be decoded.

@item -t @var{temporal_layer_id}
Signal the target @var{temporal_layer_id} to be decoded. Default to the highest

@item -s @var{INTEGER} 
Only decode @var{INTEGER} first frames.

@item -r @var{FLOAT}
Forces the frame rate to @var{FLOAT}

@end table

@c man end OPTIONS



